# Trigonometric Identities

The Pythagorean identity states that math`sin(x)^2 + cos(x)^2` equals 1 for all math`x`.

!claim pythagorean
  sin(x)^2 + cos(x)^2 = 1

From claim`pythagorean` we can derive the double angle formula.

!claim double_angle_cos
  cos(x)^2 - sin(x)^2 = 2cos(x)^2 - 1

!proof double_angle_cos
  cos(x)^2 - sin(x)^2
  = cos(x)^2 - (1 - cos(x)^2)
  = 2cos(x)^2 - 1
